    Venus sighes as she once agian tries to get the girl to come with her. 
"Watching out for who? Well, that dosent matter. What matters is that its 
cold and youre lost. Come with me back to my ship. Right now." She had 
finally lost patience with the girl, and her palms began to emit a blue glow 
to them. They were charged, and ready to send a bolt of energon at the girl.
    "Lets go. Its only going to get colder!" She barked, eyes narrowed at 
Quasar.
